<H1></H1>
<H1><B>Resolutions of ISO/IEC JTC 1/SC 34 Plenary Meeting, =
2008-04-05/09, Oslo,=20
Norway </B></H1></CENTER>National bodies and Liaison organizations =
present at=20
the closing plenary:<BR>
<P>Canada, Czech Republic, Denmark, Finland, Germany, Japan, Korea =
(Republic=20
of), Norway, South Africa, Sweden, UK, USA, Ecma International and the =
XML Guild=20
</P>
<H2><B><A name#Res1>Resolution 1: Accessibility in SC 34</B></H2>SC 34=20
notes:<BR>
<UL>
  <LI>the importance of ensuring that accessibility to people with =
disabilities=20
  is taken into account in the development of document description and=20
  processing standards<BR>
  <LI>that at its Berlin Plenary Meeting in October 2004 JTC1 =
established a=20
  Special Working Group on Accessibility (SWG-A)<BR>
  <LI>that JTC1 SWG-A has been developing a multi-part Technical Report =
PDTR=20
  29138 (Information Technology - Accessibility Considerations for =
People with=20
  Disabilities) which looks at both user needs (Parts 1 and 3) and the =
extent to=20
  which existing standards meet those needs (Part 2)<BR>
  <LI>that the importance of accessibility is recognized by other =
standards=20
  bodies, including W3C (through its WAI initiative)<BR>
  <LI>that accessibility guidelines are incorporated in ISO/IEC 26300 =
ODF<BR>
  <LI>that (through the efforts of the Canadian and New Zealand National =
Bodies=20
  in particular) significant support for accessibility has been added to =
the=20
  final text of ISO/IEC 29500 OOXML<BR></LI></UL>
<P>SC 34 resolves that accessibility considerations will be taken fully =
into=20
account in current and future projects and urges its members to review =
the work=20
of JTC1 SWG-A (especially PDTR 29138), W3C WAI and others, and to play =
an active=20
part in the implementation and further development of accessibility=20
guidelines<BR></P>
<P>SC 34 requests that the SC34 Secretariat / Japanese National Body =
make a=20
report to the next SC34 Plenary Meeting on the results of the JTC1 SWG-A =
meeting=20
in Tokyo, Japan, 16-19 June 2008.<BR></P>
<DIV align=3Dleft>
<P><B><I>Unanimous<BR></I></B></P>
<H2><B><A name=3D#Res2>Resolution 2: Response to JTC 1 SWG on Technology =

Watch</B></H2>SC 34 approves <A=20
href=3D"http://www.itscj.ipsj.or.jp/sc34/def/1016.pdf">SC 34 N 1016</A> =
as its=20
Response to JTC 1 TW0045, "Sense Engines and Molecular Architecture for =
creating=20
effective ebusiness infrastructure for the Marble Industry" and =
instructs its=20
Secretariat to forward it to the JTC 1 Secretariat.<BR></DIV>
<P><B><I>Unanimous<BR></I></B></P>
<H2><A name=3D#Res3>Resolution 3: SC 34 Representation to JTC 1 SWG on=20
Directives</H2>SC 34 notes the importance of JTC 1 SWG on Directives and =

requests its Chairman and Secretariat to monitor the activities and to =
appoint=20
its representatives on an ad hoc basis. <BR>
<P><I><B>Abstain: Canada<BR></B></I></P>
<H2><A name=3D#Res4>Resolution 4: Creation of Ad Hoc Group 1 on ISO/IEC =
29500=20
Maintenance</H2>
<P><B>Background<BR></B></P>
<P>SC 34 is the JTC 1 designated maintenance body for ISO/IEC 29500 =
(Office Open=20
XML file formats).<BR></P>
<P>The passage of ISO/IEC 29500 has instituted a new era of standards =
activity=20
in SC 34 related to document formats. ISO/IEC 29500 does not represent =
an=20
isolated phenomenon, since SC 34 is also responsible for ISO/IEC 26300 =
and for=20
interoperability between these and other projects.<BR></P>
<P>SC 34 envisages the creation of three distinct working groups that =
meet the=20
needs of:<BR></P>
<OL>
  <LI>ISO/IEC 29500<BR>
  <LI>ISO/IEC 26300<BR>
  <LI>Work on interoperability/harmonization between document format=20
  standards<BR></LI></OL>
<P>and wishes to incorporate existing expertise on these =
standards.<BR></P>
<P>For these reasons, SC 34 hereby establishes an ad hoc group pursuant =
to the=20
JTC 1 Directives, clause 2.6.2, for investigating how the first of these =
groups=20
may be set up most effectively.<BR></P>
<P><B>Terms of Reference<BR></B></P>
<P>The terms of reference for the group are as follows:<BR></P>
<OL>
  <LI>The task to be completed by the group is to advise its convenor on =

  creation of a document proposing structures and mechanisms for onward =
work on=20
  ISO/IEC 29500. Onward work is defined as:<BR>
  <UL>
    <LI>Maintenance as provided for by the JTC 1 Directives (in =
particular=20
    Section 15 - Maintenance of International Standards)<BR>
    <LI>Handling new work items directly and exclusively related to =
ISO/IEC=20
    29500 (e.g. creation of new Parts of this Standard or evolution of =
this=20
    standard)<BR></LI></UL>
  <P>The proposal shall be drafted by the convenor as one or more =
resolutions=20
  (with supporting explanatory material) that may be discussed, revised =
and=20
  adopted by SC 34.<BR></P>
  <P>The ad hoc group should consider the following factors in making =
its=20
  recommendations to the convenor:<BR></P>
  <OL>
    <P>a) A new working group should be created in SC 34 for the purpose =
of=20
    maintenance of ISO/IEC 29500 pursuant to Section 15 of the JTC 1 =
Directives=20
    for standards maintenance.<BR>b) Editors and editing teams should be =

    nominated as well as mechanisms for the nomination of editors and =
editing=20
    teams for ISO/IEC 29500.<BR>c) Transparency of process, consistent =
with JTC=20
    1 Directives, is a goal of the recommended process.<BR>d) =
Consideration=20
    should be given to how Ecma and ISO/IEC versions of ISO/IEC 29500 =
may be=20
    best kept synchronized.<BR>e) The proposal should recommend ways in =
which=20
    onward work on ISO/IEC 29500 may be carried out in as timely a way =
as=20
    possible, without recourse to the accelerated mechanisms of PAS or =
Fast=20
    Track procedures.<BR></P></OL>
  <LI>The ad hoc group shall make its proposal to SC 34 for =
consideration at its=20
  plenary scheduled for 2008-10-01, at Jeju Island, Korea. A draft =
proposal=20
  shall be made available to SC 34 one month before the plenary.<BR>
  <LI>The ad hoc group shall be open to participation from all SC 34 =
members,=20
  subgroup members, and liaison bodies. Participants shall be nominated =
by these=20
  bodies to the SC 34 secretariat in the usual way.<BR>
  <LI>The ad hoc group shall be convened by Dr Alex Brown, as nominated =
by the=20
  UK National Body (BSi).<BR>
  <LI>Administration and support for the ad hoc group=92s activities =
shall be=20
  provided by the SC 34 Secretariat.<BR>
  <LI>The ad hoc group shall arrange face-to-face, telephone and =
electronic=20
  meetings as required in accord with the provisions of the JTC 1 =
Directives.=20
  The first face-to-face meeting shall take place in early July in =
London,=20
  UK.<BR></LI></OL><B><I>Unanimous<BR></I></B>
<H2><A name=3D#Res5>Resolution 5: Creation of Ad Hoc Group 2 on ISO/IEC =
29500=20
Comment Collection</H2>
<P>[Note: This group will focus only on the initial collection of =
comments on=20
ISO/IEC 29500. The long-term maintenance of ISO/IEC 29500 will be =
addressed by=20
Ad Hoc Group 1.]<BR></P>
<P>ISO/IEC JTC 1/SC 34 establishes Ad Hoc Group 2 in accordance with =
subclause=20
2.6.2 of the JTC 1 Directives, with the following terms of =
reference:<BR></P>
<UL>
  <LI><B>Definition of the task:<BR></B>
  <UL>
    <LI>To define and put into operation a mechanism to compile a list =
of=20
    comments on ISO/IEC 29500 received from NBs, liaisons, and the =
general=20
    public.<BR>
    <LI>To publish the on-going list as an open document on the SC 34=20
    website.<BR></LI></UL>
  <LI><B>Time frame: </B>The collection mechanism is to become =
operational=20
  within 90 days from the end of the April 2008 ISO/IEC JTC 1/SC 34 =
plenary.=20
  Once this is operational, collection will continue until a long-term=20
  maintenance process is operational.<BR>
  <LI><B>Membership:</B> Open to ISO/IEC JTC 1/SC 34 P and O members, =
liaison=20
  organizations, and subgroup representatives.<BR>
  <LI><B>Convener: </B>Makoto Murata (JP).<BR>
  <LI><B>Meeting arrangements: </B>Work will be handled primarily by =
email, with=20
  optional telephone conference calls at dates and times to be=20
  announced.<BR></LI></UL>
<P><B><I>Unanimous</I></B></P>
<P></P>
<H2><A name=3D#Res6>Resolution 6: Encouragement to NBs and liaisons to =
report=20
possible defects in ISO/IEC 29500</H2>
<P>As soon as the Ad Hoc Group 2's comment collection mechanism is =
operational,=20
NBs and liaisons are encouraged to use that mechanism to report possible =

editorial or technical defects in ISO/IEC 29500.<BR></P>
<P><B><I>Unanimous</I></B></P>
<P></P>
<H2><A name=3D#Res7>Resolution 7: Liaison statement to Ecma TC 45 on the =

maintenance of ISO/IEC 29500 (Office Open XML)</H2>SC 34 approves the =
liaison=20
statement contained in <A=20
href=3D"http://www.itscj.ipsj.or.jp/sc34/open/1018.htm">SC 34 N 1018</A> =
and=20
instructs its Secretariat to forward it to Ecma TC 45.<BR>
<P><B><I>Unanimous</I></B></P>
<P></P>
<H2><A name=3D#Res8>Resolution 8: Distribution of Final text of DIS =
29500</H2>
<P>SC 34 requests the ITTF and the SC34 secretariat to distribute the =
already=20
received final text of DIS 29500 to the SC 34 members in accordance with =
JTC 1=20
directives section 13.12 as soon as possible, but not later than May 1st =
2008.=20
Access to this document is important for the success of various ISO/IEC =
29500=20
maintenance activities.<BR></P>
<P><B><I>Unanimous<BR></I></B></P>
<P></P>
<H2><A name=3D#Res9>Resolution 9: Minor Revision of ISO/IEC =
19757-2/Amd.1 and=20
ISO/IEC 19757-4</H2>SC 34 approves the disposition of comments on DCOR =
to=20
ISO/IEC 19757-2/Amd.1 and ISO/IEC 19757-4 contained in <A=20
href=3D"http://www.itscj.ipsj.or.jp/sc34/def/1019.htm">SC 34 N 1019</A> =
and N 1020=20
respectively. SC 34 requests the ITTF to publish the minor revisions of =
ISO/IEC=20
19757-2/Amd. 1 and ISO/IEC 19757-4 by incorporating the final texts of =
the=20
DCOR.<BR>
<P><B><I>Unanimous<BR></I></B></P>
<P></P>
